{
  "texts": [
    "The only exception is QA, where we do not evaluate \"Appropriateness\" since the dimension considers coherence with respect to a dialogue history but QA only has question-answer exchanges.",
    "Instead, we extend the protocol foot_1 by proposing a new dimension for QA:",
    "• Validity: the response includes adequate information to answer the question.",
    "For TOD we do not include a dimension to evaluate whether the response is in line with user requirements, as this can be measured automatically (via dialogue state tracking metrics e.g., Joint Goal Accuracy).",
    "The dimensions can either have a positive or negative answer value, as well as \"I don't know\" to avoid forcing erroneous judgments on any of the two sides."
  ]
}